news.title: Mohali: Gmada proposes ₹800 per sq yard cut in enhancement charges for sectors 76–80
news.para: Gmada has proposed reducing enhancement charges by Rs 800 per square yard for over 30,000 plot allottees in sectors 76-80. The decision awaits state government approval, pending a comparative review of charge calculation models used by Noida and Haryana development authorities.

news.title: IIFL Home Finance raises $100 million loan from Asian Infrastructure Investment Bank
news.para: IIFL Home Finance, backed by ADIA, has secured a $100 million loan from AIIB to boost affordable housing in India. The funds will be used for lending to economically weaker sections and developers of low-cost apartments, promoting green building practices. This five-year loan, with an 8.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body tells residents to raze 172 houses in 15 days
news.para: Ghaziabad Development Authority issued demolition notices to 172 households in Babu Jagjivan Ram Colony. GDA claims the colony is built on park land. Residents are given 15 days to demolish structures. An NGT petition brought the issue to light. A review meeting is scheduled. Residents express concern over the sudden notice after 50 years.

news.title: Maharashtra CM to hand over first lot of BDD flats in Worli on July 21
news.para: Chief Minister Devendra Fadnavis is set to hand over keys to the first 556 BDD flats in Worli on July 21, marking a significant milestone in the redevelopment project. These 500 sq ft flats will be allocated to tenants who were previously moved to transit accommodations.

news.title: CIDCO to allow conversion of residential leasehold plots to freehold
news.para: Maharashtra government approved a plan. This plan allows owners of residential plots allotted by CIDCO to convert their leasehold properties to freehold. CIDCO formed a committee to manage applications. The scheme applies to various plot allotments.

news.title: YEIDA to hold draw for residential plot scheme in Sector 18 on July 11
news.para: YEIDA is set to conduct a draw of lots for its Sector 18 residential plot scheme, featuring 276 plots, after receiving over 54,000 applications. The draw, supervised by retired High Court judges for transparency, will be broadcast live.

news.title: Bhubaneswar development body lets housing society cut power, water over dues
news.para: In a first for Odisha, the Bhubaneswar Development Authority has empowered an association of allottees to disconnect essential services to residents who fail to pay monthly maintenance fees. The order, citing the Odisha Apartment Act of 2023, addresses the issue of wilful non-payment by some flat owners, promoting shared responsibility within apartment complexes.

news.title: Telangana RERA pulls up Kavuri Forest Nest developer over poor upkeep
news.para: Telangana RERA has instructed Kavuri Forest Nest developer to maintain community common areas as per the sale agreement, following complaints from villa owners about service reductions and extra charges. Residents cited issues like discontinued road sweeping and poor upkeep of amenities at the Tukkuguda project.

news.title: Noida authority may challenge Allahabad HC order on lease rent waivers
news.para: Noida Authority will challenge Allahabad High Court's decision. The court had cancelled lease rent waivers given to real estate firms. These waivers were initially granted under the 'zero period' relief. The Authority cites the need to protect revenue.

news.title: Telangana RERA halts 'Shrivari's Brundavanam' project after buyer complaints
news.para: Telangana Real Estate Regulatory Authority has stopped the Shrivari's Brundavanam housing project. This action follows complaints from buyers about delays. Shrivari Constructions failed to deliver flats as promised. TGRERA has restricted the developer from further sales.

news.title: Bain Capital sells 1.9% unitholding in Embassy REIT for ₹691 crore
news.para: Bain Capital divested a 1.9% stake in Embassy Office Parks REIT for ₹691 crore through an open market transaction. APAC Company XXIII, a Bain Capital affiliate, sold over 1.78 crore units at an average price of ₹388 each. Embassy Office Parks REIT units subsequently slipped 1.95% on the BSE.

news.title: Blackstone ups offer to $666 million in battle for UK's Warehouse REIT
news.para: Blackstone, a U.S. private equity firm, has increased its offer for Warehouse REIT to approximately £489 million, surpassing Tritax Big Box REIT's agreed deal. This move highlights the trend of U.S. companies acquiring undervalued British assets.

news.title: Zomato founder buys apartment for ₹52.3 crore in DLF Camellias project in Gurugram
news.para: Zomato's co-founder, Deepinder Goyal, invested Rs 52.3 crore in a luxurious 11,000 sq ft apartment within DLF Camellias, Gurugram, back in August 2022, with registration completed this March. Experts estimate the property's current value soars between Rs 125 crore and Rs 150 crore, reflecting Gurugram's surging housing market.

news.title: Insolvency sale of Frankfurt office tower to test fragile German market
news.para: Administrators are seeking buyers for Frankfurt's Trianon skyscraper after its owner faced insolvency due to Germany's office property downturn. The 186m tower, partly occupied by the Bundesbank, is on the market for less than its 2018 sale price of €670 million, burdened by €370 million in debt.

news.title: UK: Vistry's pre-tax profit slumps nearly 34% in H1 2025
news.para: Vistry anticipates a significant drop in first-half 2025 profits due to persistent affordability challenges and rising costs, despite government support for affordable housing. The British homebuilder expects increased government funding to boost new contracts in the latter half of 2025, driving future growth. While demand recovery is anticipated, profit margins may remain pressured by bulk affordable housing deals.

news.title: Logan Group wins bondholder approval for Shenzhen unit's debt restructuring
news.para: Logan Group, a Shenzhen-based developer, has received approval for its debt restructuring plan. This covers several onshore bonds. Bondholders have options including asset conversion, swaps, cash repurchase, and equity rights.

news.title: Ignore earlier order on India Cements: CBI
news.para: The CBI has requested the High Court to disregard its previous judgment that acquitted India Cements in the quid pro quo case involving YS Jaganmohan Reddy, as the agency has appealed to the Supreme Court. This appeal is currently pending. The request was made during a hearing on Dalmia Cements' petition to quash the case against them.

news.title: Peninsula Land acquires land parcels in Alibaug and Karjat
news.para: Peninsula Land, an Ashok Piramal Group company, has expanded its plotted development business by acquiring two significant land parcels. The acquisitions include 11 acres in Sogaon, Alibaug, and approximately 29 acres in Bhilawale, Karjat.

news.title: Telangana RERA fines agent for promoting unregistered flats, fraud transactions
news.para: Telangana RERA fined a real estate agent Rs 6.17 lakh for promoting an unregistered project and impersonating the builder while issuing receipts. Aaditri Housing was directed to complete and register a flat for a complainant after mortgage release, facing further penalties for delays.

news.title: Mittal Builders, HoABL to invest ₹2,000 crore on 11-acre project in Mumbai region
news.para: Mittal Builders partners with House of Abhinandan Lodha for a housing project. The project is in the Mumbai Metropolitan Region. Investment is estimated at Rs 2,000 crore. The project will span 11 acres.
